description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you committed to delivering the best of care through the best of people? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Consultant in Emergency General Surgery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;£82,096 - £110,683 per annum / pro rata&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Consultant Surgeon who shares our ambition and vision to deliver the Best of Care by the Best People and has the drive to take us forward, by ensuring the Trust continues to be the first choice for patients and our staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Consultant in Emergency general surgery with an interest in laparoscopy, day surgery and endoscopy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join an established team of Emergency surgeons, as we double our investment in Consultant-led services in this area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are expanding our emergency and ambulatory surgery service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a forward looking Emergency surgeon to join our team of 12 existing general and emergency surgeons.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The surgeons share the on call equally. The successful applicant will be encouraged to develop the ambulatory emergency service with our 2 existing emergency surgeons. There are plans to appoint a fourth emergency surgeon in the coming months taking the on call to 1:12. Experience in endoscopy is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant will also be encouraged to develop their skills in advanced endoscopy. The applicant will have a regular day surgery theatre in addition to the emergency theatre and be expected to develop the range of procedures undertaken in the day surgery unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust and its employees are all committed to creating and maintaining a fair and supportive working environment and culture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of our commitment to you, we will give you the opportunity to utilise and enhance your talents to assist us in the development of shaping the future of Medway NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust offers a number of apprenticeships and training opportunities in Leadership and Management, Business Services, Finance, Accounting, Human Resources, Clinical Support Work, Research and Innovation, Nursing Associate and Assistant Practitioner alongside our in-house comprehensive clinical pathways.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our hope is that our education pathways will play a key role in enabling you to challenge the practices of the past and build capability for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is committed to the protection of children, young people, their families and vulnerable adults accessing its services. Promoting the message that “safeguarding is everyone’s business” is vital to ensure our patients are protected and safe from abuse. To this end you must comply with Trust’s and the Kent and Medway Safeguarding Board’s policies on safeguarding children, young people and vulnerable adults.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name:- Mr Ibrahim Ahmed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title:- Consultant Surgeon&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address:- ibrahimahmed@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number:- 01634 838942&lt;/p&gt;
